the 10 frog corpses from the group camping the rares.<br>
<br>
As for VP, I can see arguments both ways.  I've had my key for a year now, getting it back in my low-50's in a very small guild when Trak was still something to be feared, but didn't get to step foot into the zone until just under a month ago.  I guess the main thing that's fun about being in VP is that, well, it's keyed.  Very few people set foot into VP on my server, it just feels like an accomplishment to just zone in.  Far far more people have been in NToV, since you can bring along 100 people whenever you desire, plus monks made runs to PoM months before anyone was able to kill dragons there.  If there were no key, the zone would be trivial as hell - the only thing stopping it from being annihilated is the supply of keys.<br>
<br>
That said, yes, it could use a revamp.  75% of the drops are weapons that are so outdated, that stuff that drops in Maiden's Eye have comparable stats.  The class robes are seriously out of date (except the wizard one), the class staffs are seriously horrendous (again, except the wizard one), there are necklaces that drop that pale in comparison to your average WW talisman, and all that good stuff.  That, plus with the purely idiotic respawn time on the trash, a raid consists of sitting in a safe spot and waiting an hour for the pull team to pull a dragon, then CoHing the entire raid to another spot, then dragon pull again, etc.  Not exactly the most exciting raid.<br>
<br>
Still, the zone still has it's limited nice drops, and is a nice change of pace, but it can get old quick.  Even if it is revamped, I hope they do keep the key requirement in, if only for the reason that it prevents zerging stuff, at least for a while.  That's what made zones like Sleeper's so hard initially - the mobs weren't that hard, but you didn't have too many people to bring with.  The golems were a bit of a challenge with 2 groups.  If any ol' guild could bring in 80 any time they wanted, the zone would suck.  On the same note, Silverwing would be rocked repeatedly if there were no keys by like 20 guilds.  Getting buffs like Primal Essence, as a result, is more of a reward now than a handout. <p><a href="http://www.reconstructed.nu/profile.php?pid=119">Baron Aledar Boomcaster</a><br>Sorcerer of <a href="http://www.reconstructed.nu/">Reconstructed</a>, E'ci<br><img src="http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bwa/diegate.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubonegruel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bonegruel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/19/02 3:20:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13037.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VP keyless on Test?</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I really do understand why people don't want the VP keys removed, and I really want to agree with them.... it's just that I keep thinking of the dragons being perma-farmed and zillions and millions of copies of Sunstrike and Lure of Ice and Tears of Prexus being auctioned in EC for under 10kpp.... and my self control slips a little bit :  )<br>
